topic: Sport Workflow Series ("F1 pilots explorative search")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for obtaining the team of a given  F1 driver  and also the F1 competitions in which they participated
goals.2: Identify the BGP that connects a F1 team to a parent company
goals.3: How many F1 drivers and F1 teams exist in each country?
goals.4: Compare number of F1 drivers to their nationality
goals.4.1: Is there some driver that joined a team in their own country?
goals.4.2: Which team employed the larger number of drivers?
goals.4.3: For each country , which are the teams and drivers with the highest number of F1 race participations

search_workflow.narrative: 4.1 drivers that joined teams from their own original country
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?driverName ?teamName ?countryName where{{ ?driver wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?driverName ; wdt:P27 ?country1 ; wdt:P54 ?team . ?team wdt:P17 ?country2 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?teamName . ?country1 <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . filter(?country1 = ?country2) . }}

search_workflow.narrative: 4.2 which team employed the largest amount of drivers?
search_workflow.query: select ?teamName (count(*) as ?n) where{{ ?driver wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 . ?driver wdt:P54 ?team . ?team wdt:P31 wd:Q10497835 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?teamName . }} group by ?teamName order by desc(?n) limit 10

search_workflow.narrative: let's double check if scuderia ferrari employed 15 drivers in total
search_workflow.query: select ?driverName where{{ ?driver wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 ; wdt:P54 wd:Q169898 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?driverName . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
4.3 for each country, the drivers with highest number of f1 race participations
let's try again to find a property connecting a gp with drivers
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?gp wdt:P361 ?championship . ?championship <http://schema.org/name> ?cName . filter regex(?cName, '.*formula one.*', 'i') . ?gp ?property ?driver . ?driver wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}

search_workflow.narrative: after all these trials, i missed "participant", let's see what it is
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?driverName ?gpName where{{ ?gp wdt:P361 ?championship . ?championship <http://schema.org/name> ?cName . filter regex(?cName, '.*formula one.*', 'i') . ?gp wdt:P710 ?driver . ?gp <http://schema.org/name> ?gpName . ?driver wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 . ?driver <http://schema.org/name> ?driverName }} limit 50

search_workflow.narrative:
we missed an important property
going back up i found an interestin property exiting the 2016 championship
[('p', 'http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/P3450'), ('name', 'sports season of league or competition')]
let's check it out
search_workflow.query: select ?o ?name where{{ wd:Q17455748 wdt:P3450 ?o . ?o <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
we can try to use that property and that entity to filter out formula 1 championship instead of using regex on the name
let's try now and list all participations for schumacher
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?gpName where{{ ?gp wdt:P710 wd:Q9671 . ?gp wdt:P3450 wd:Q1968 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?gpName . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's count the participations for each driver then
search_workflow.query: select ?driverName (count(*) as ?n) where{{ ?gp wdt:P710 ?driver . ?driver wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 . ?driver <http://schema.org/name> ?driverName . }} group by ?driverName

search_workflow.narrative: really not many participations... let's answer to point 4.3 nonetheless
search_workflow.query: select ?driverName ?countryName ?max where{{ ?d <http://schema.org/name> ?driverName . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . {{ select ?country (max(?n) as ?max) where{{ {{ select ?driver ?country (count(*) as ?n) where{{ ?gp wdt:P710 ?driver . ?driver wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 . ?driver wdt:P27 ?country . }} group by ?driver ?country }} }} }} {{ select ?d ?c (count(*) as ?cnt) where{{ ?gp wdt:P710 ?d . ?d wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 . ?d wdt:P27 ?c . }} group by ?d ?c }} filter(?max = ?cnt && ?country = ?c) }}
